The course introduces theoretical and practical approaches of gender-based violence, and is addressed to students of social sciences and medicine and other disciplines, who want to know more about the phenomenon of violence or will need this knowledge in their further work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to introduce the terminology, typology and theoretical approaches related to gender-based violence, as well as to give an overview on effects of violence on victims, general principles of victim assistance, and legal regulations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course the student:     Knows basic terms and theories related to gender-based violence.     Knows main types of gender-based violence.     Understands the gender issues in the topic of violence     Knows the signs and health effects of violence.     Can critically evaluate attitudes and myths related to violence.     Has an overview of legal regulation in the field of gender-based violence and victim assistance.
